cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.SI 

This paper proposes a novel method for multi-view semi-supervised classification, which involves learning a latent representation and performing graph learning and label propagation based on the learned latent representation. This method is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given the focus on classification and the use of graph-based methods, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category.
